# InfoHub Project Rules (.cursorrules)

## Project Context
You are an expert full-stack developer working on **InfoHub**, a web platform for the CPNV Info association. The site is a central hub for students and teachers of the IT section.

## Technical Stack Constraints
- **Language:** PHP (mandatory).
- **Database:** MySQL.
- **Frontend:** Responsive Design (Mobile-first).
- **Hosting:** Must be compatible with Swisscenter (infohub.mycpnv.ch).

## Core Business Logic
### 1. Authentication
- Implementation: Register/Login system with hashed passwords.
- Future-proofing: Design to eventually allow CPNV SSO (eduvaud.ch).

### 2. Modules & Features
- **News (Actualités):** Image upload + Text (Simple or Markdown).
- **Concours du mois:** Special news item or dedicated entity featured on the homepage.
- **Ads (Annonces):** - Categories: À vendre, À donner, Covoiturage, Demande d'aide, Petits boulots.
    - Fields: Image, description, category, price (optional), contact info, pub date, expiry date (7 days default), status (visible/hidden).
    - Interaction: Discussion/comments section under each ad.
- **Pubs:** Two most recent ads/pubs featured at the bottom of the homepage.

### 3. Roles & Permissions
- **Users (Students/Teachers):** Can submit news, submit ads, and comment.
- **Admins:** Must validate/refuse all user submissions before they go live. Can hide/reactivate content and post directly.

## UI/UX Requirements (Homepage Structure)
- Header: Banner with image and logo.
- Main: Featured "Concours du mois".
- News: Preview of the 2 latest/featured articles.
- Ads: Preview of the 2 latest/featured announcements.
- Footer: 2 latest "Pubs" (special ads).
- Navigation: Menu for News, Ads, and Pubs.

## Implementation Guidelines
- Ensure all user inputs are sanitized (SQL Injection & XSS protection).
- Follow PSR coding standards for PHP.
- Implement a clear validation workflow for all user-generated content.